verbose_text: During MMW irradiation at the highest level of incident power density (IPD) of 4 mW/cm 2, there was a gradual hyperpolarization of the RMP and gradual decrease of the firing rate (XREF_FIG, A and C), both of which returned to preirradiation levels (with some overshot) within 30 s after the MMW power was terminated.
evidence: level of incident power density (IPD) of 4 mW/cm 2
